  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To profane (βεβηλῶσαι)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The word is akin to βηλός, threshold, and βαίνω, to step; and its fundamental idea, therefore, is that of overstepping the threshold of sacred places. The word profane is the Latin pro fanum, in front of the sanctuary; that which is kept outside the fane because unholy.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "We laid hold",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The best texts omit all after these words as far as by examining. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]